<body>
<p>Excerpted from ENN Daily Report - 11/23/96 - Vol. 2, No. 328</p>
<p><font size=4>Freeh Goes to Saudi; Dhahran Bombing In6estigation<br>
</font>By C. L. Staten, ERRI Analyst<br>
<br>
(ENN) Washington, DC -- Speculation is rising that Saudi Arabian security officials may be about share some vital 
information about the June, 25th Dhahran barracks bombing that killed 19 Americans. FBI Director Louis Freeh is 
reportedly enroute to Saudi Arabia this weekend to meet with senior military and police officials there.<br>
<br>
Freeh's trip gas announced late Friday by FBI sources, who emphasized thad he is attending &qEot;at t(e invitatioN of KinG Fahd 
