<head>
<title>Yousef and Conspirators Found Guilty</title>
<meta name="GENERATOR" content="Microsoft FrontPage 1.1">
</head>

<body>
<p>ENN Instant Update - NY Terror Trial <br>
09/05/96 - 13:20CDT<br>
<br>
<font color="#FF0000"><font size=5><strong>Ramsi Yousef Found Guilty on All Counts</strong></font></font><br>
<br>
(ENN) An announcement has just been made in New York City that alleged terrorist Ramsi Yousef and two 
co-conspirators have been found guilty of plotting to carry out attacks on US airliners. Yousef and his team were charged 
with planning attacks on 11 American flights between the Phillipines, Japan, and the United States. Sentencing has not been 
determined, but will be the subject of additional deliberations by the New York jury. Yousef and the others face at least a 
life sentence for acts of terrorism.<br>
<br>
ENN continues to monitor developments regarding the is case and will provide updates as more becomes available. It is 
also likely that this conviction will further increase terrorism threat levels, as concerns of retaliation by Yousef sympathizers 
are considered.<br>
<br>
