About ERRI/ENN:
<p>
The Emergency Response &amp; Research Institute (ERRI) is an emergency service and military 'think-tank' that researches, analyzes, and reports on disasters, emergency service operations, and military issues.  ERRI is staffed by veteran emergency responders and military personnel, all of whom have  more than fifteen (15) years of service in some of the nation's leading emergency and military agencies.  
<p>
A particular area of  ERRI expertise involves its on-going, twelve (12) year, study of terrorists and international terrorism. EmergencyNet NEWS is produced by ERRI and is available to interested emergency agencies and media outlets by subscription.  <p>
