<HEAD>
<TITLE>Israeli Defense Industries- New Weapon</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Israeli Defense Industries Announce New Assault Weapon</H2>

<IMG SRC="/isrl203.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT>

The new Israeli weapon of the future...the M-203. The weapon, still not in use, is reportedly first going to be issued to the elite commando-reconnaissance units of the IDF in the future.
<P> 
<B>Some facts and figures about the weapon. </B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>1. Designed by Israel Military Industries. 
<LI>2. The IDF gave the inner mechanism and barrel to artists and told them  to design the gun to fit the body. 
<LI>3. There are no sharp edges on the gun. 
<LI>4. It has an aerodynamic design - nothing to catch clothing or fingers on.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Some of the highlights: </B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>1. On the grip, directly behind the trigger, there are built in handgrips,  rubber bumps, protruding from the weapon so that a soldier never looses  his grip, even after holding it a long time. 
<LI>2. The shoulder stock is contoured to the anatomy of the shoulder. It  "fits" in the shoulder and doesn't move.  
<LI>3. The handgrip by the trigger has protection so that in the event of slippage, the hand cannot be injured. 
<LI>4. The spacing around the trigger allows for the infantry soldier to  comfortably operate the weapon while wearing warm gloves.
</UL>
<P>
<B>Specs</B>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI>1. The gun, including night sights, and a magazine with 30 rounds, weighs 3.5  kg. That is 1 kg. more than the M-16.
<LI>2. The weapon is classified as an assault rifle with multiple uses. It is  good for anti-terror missions, because it can be equipped with a silencer. An optical long distance "sight" can also be added. It comes standard with a laser sight enabling it to be used in night or low-light combat.
</UL>
<P>
Sorry - the caliber of the weapon is not specified at this time. 
<P> 
From ENN Archives: 02/96--Source: Special thanks to the SNS-News Service-Israel
