<P>

2 Mississippi v. Minnick, 111 S. Ct. 486 (1990).
<P>

3 Courts also have begun to impose similar limitations on a
suspect's ability to invoke the right to silence. Coleman v.
Singletary, 30 F.3d 1420 (11th Cir. 1994).
<P>

4 114 S.Ct. 2350 (1994).
<P>

5 Although Davis was not in custody at the time of the
interrogation, military law required that he be advised that he
was a suspect and informed of his Miranda rights.
<P>

6 The conviction was upheld by the U.S. Court of Military
