<TITLE>USDOJ Announces New Web Site</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
For Immediate Release: 02/16/96-15:00CST
<BR>
EmergencyNet News Service
<P>
<H2>U.S. Dept. of Justice Provides New On-Line Statistics</H2>

The U.S. Dept. of Justice Statistics today announced that they are now making a large body of crime statistics available on a new government website.  According to B.J.S. Director Jan Chaiken, data sets on murder rates, drug usage, domestic abuse violence, gunsused in crimes, and prison populations will be made available at:
<P>
<A HREF="http://www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/"><B>Click here to go to the BOJ Statistic Database: www.ojp.usdoj.gov/bjs/</B></A>
<P>
According to Chaiken, data will be available from the mid-1970s to the present time and additional information will be added the website on an ongoing basis.  Chaiken said that the new website was part of a larger goal to make government information instantly available to those doing research and studying issues of crime in the United States.
<P>
