<BR>
               
<H2>   Smoky Fire in Empire State Building</H2>
<P>

Chicago, IL., (ENN) November 21, 1995 --Preliminary reports are being
received by ENN of a fire in a sub-basement of the 102 story
Empire State Building. According to fire department sources, a
third alarm has been transmitted and several ambulances have
been dispatched to the scene. Reports are being received of
rescues being performed on the upper floors of the building. An
unidentified EMS dispatcher said that several people may have
suffered smoke inhalation injuries.
<P>

An eyewitness told ENN that smoke from what is being called an
"electical vault fire" had apparently spread through several of
the upper floors of the building and that there was smoke in
some of the stairways.  The man also told ENN that at least some
of the elevators were not working and people were being
evacuated down the stairways.
<P>

There are no reports of deaths, and an indeterminate number of
injuries, at this time, as an evacuation continues.  ENN is
gathering additional details and will provide updates as the
information is made available.
<P>

