<TITLE>4th Alarm Fire in Queens; YMCA Rescues</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
EmergencyNet News Service
<BR>
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE: 23:50CST-01/23/96
<P>
                        <center> **ENNNEWS FLASH**</center>


<H2>4th Alarm Fire in YMCA</H2>
By: Clark Staten
<P>
Chicago, IL, January 23, 1996 -- ENN is recieving numerous
reports of a fire at Bowen and Northern Blvd. in the borough of
Queens, NYC. The fire has rapidly progressed to a 4th alarm. 
Numerous People are reported trapped and numerous ladder
companies are affecting rescues.  The fire building is reported
as a fully occupied YMCA.
<P> 

The building is a five story brick with heavy smoke and fire on the 3rd and 4th floor.  The exact number of injuries or deaths are unknown at this time, but at
least twenty people have been rescued from the building at the
time of this report.  More as it becomes available....
<P>

