<HEAD>
<TITLE>15 Year Old Hijacks Bus; Kills Self</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<B>ENN 5/15/96  08:59CDT</B>
<P>
<H2>15 Year Old Hijacks Bus; Kills Self</H2>
<P>

TAYLORSVILLE, UTAH (ENN) - A 15-year-old student who was armed with a .357 Magnum revolver hijacked a school bus in suburban Salt Lake City on Wednesday.  He shot the driver, led police on a high-speed chase, crashed the bus into a house and in the end shot and killed himself.  The subject was identified as Justin Allgood.  Police said that they believed he put the gun in his mouth and killed himself before the bus crashed into the house.
<P>

Printed newspaper obituaries of three close friends of Allgood's were found in his pocket.  The friends had all died in traffic accidents in the last two weeks, including one who died on Monday.
<P>

Salt Lake County Sheriff Aaron Kennard said, "All the information we have is he's a good kid who has gone through some personal tragedies in his life that have pushed him over the edge."
<P>

Sheriff's police said that the subject boarded the bus at 0720 MDT on Tuesday morning.  He brandished a revolver and ordered the bus driver and one of his friend's to get off the bus.
<P>

The bus driver said to Allgood, "You better not take that to school or you could get in pretty bad trouble."  The bus driver held out her hand for the gun.  Without a word, Allgood shot the 40-year-old driver in the thigh.
<P>

The subject then took the wheel of the bus as other students scrambled to get off.  Allgood then led police on a 30-block high-speed chase through the suburban town.  During the chase, the bus rammed a car, ran over a chain-link fence, jumped a two-foot-wide creek and then crashed into a house.  Half of the bus landed inside the home of a retired sheriff's deputy.
<P>

The owner of the home was still in bed when the bus crashed into his living room.  The retired deputy, not knowing what was happening, grabbed his gun and ran outside.  There, police officers tackled the man and slightly injured his shoulder.
<P>

A police SWAT team was called to the scene and fired tear gas into the bus. But, it was too late, and officers then found Allgood, strapped to the drivers seat, with a self-inflicted gunshot wound to the mouth.  The bus driver, who was shot in the thigh, was reported to be in stable condition at a local hospital.
<P>
(c) EmergencyNet News Service, 1996, All rights Reserved.
<P>
