<TITLE>NJ Police Officer Dies in Pursuit</TITLE>
<!-- Comment Here -->
</HEAD>
<BODY>
For Immediate Release: 17:00EST-11/24/95
<BR>
<H3>NEW JERSEY POLICE OFFICER DIES FROM INJURIES</H3>
<BR>
<H4>Motor Vehicle Accident During Pursuit</H4>
<BR>
By James J. Fay, NYC Metro Correspondent
<P>

Police Officer Thomas Haughton of the Garwood, NJ, Police Department, died today, Friday, November 24, from injuries sustained from a motor vehicle accident while in pursuit of another vehicle. The accident occurred in the adjacent town of Westfield on Tuesday (11/21/95)  of this week at approximately 22:30 hrs. EST.
<P> 
The 27 year old officer was reportedly chasing another vehicle for a broken tail light violation. The damage to the police vehicle was reported to be extensive. Haughton's major injuries were reported to be to his head as a result of being thrown from the vehicle. Officer Haughton was a Garwood Police Officer for two and a half years.

ENN sends its condolences and prayers to the family and friends of Officer Haughton.
<P>
(c) EmergencyNet NEWS Service, 1995, All Rights reserved.
